South African Communist Party (SACP) secretary general Chris Hani was shot and killed at his Boksburg, East Rand home driveway on this day in 1993.Various programmes have been planned by the City of Ekurhuleni to commemorate the 24th anniversary of the assassination of struggle icon Chris Hani starting with a wreath-laying ceremony on Monday morning which will be led by President Jacob Zuma.The wreath-laying ceremony will be held at Thomas Nkobi Memorial Park in Boksburg. It will be followed in the evening by a memorial lecture at the Boksburg Civic Centre which will be delivered by newly-appointed finance minister Malusi Gigaba.